OL,5,GThere have been a few technical
OL,6,Ggremlins with the cameras in BBC News'
OL,7,GStudio B in recent weeks.
OL,9,FWe've perhaps become accustomed to
OL,10,Fseeing the automated cameras in Studio
OL,11,FE going walkies over the years. Such
OL,12,Fincidents are still rare in Studio B.
OL,14,FBut tonight was one of those rare
OL,15,Fexceptions. At the start of the weather
OL,16,Fsegment on the BBC News at Ten, the
OL,17,Fcamera started to swing around.
OL,19,FWithin seconds, there was a manual
OL,20,Fintervention to restore the shot on
OL,21,Fweather presenter Helen Willetts.
OL,3,CCamera mishap during the BBC News at
OL,4,CTen
